description: The military parade celebrating Nazi Germany's defeat was postponed from 9 May due to the lockdown.
title: Russia holds World War Two victory parade in coronavirus shadow
title_page: Russia holds World War Two victory parade in coronavirus shadow - BBC News
maintext: Nazi Germany ended all its military operations at 23:01 Central European Time on 8 May 1945. Russia, former Soviet Union states and some eastern European nations celebrate victory on 9 May, as - because of the change in time zone - the surrender came early in the morning the next day for those countries.
